The paper deals with the processing of historical newspaper page images, which involves text extraction, topic extraction, and document retrieval. These tasks are typically associated with information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP), which are covered by the cs.IR and cs.CL sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of machine learning techniques for preprocessing and representation, which falls under the cs.DL sub-category. The paper also discusses the challenges of working with low-quality images, which suggests the use of computer vision (CV) techniques, covered by the cs.CV sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the development of a user interface for document viewing and retrieval, which falls under the cs.HC sub-category.
